In such a situation, it&#39;s good to run a &#39;Threads Report&#39; to see what
the laggard thread is doing; it might be legitimately in the middle of
a long download.

Have you set maximum lengths/times for any one fetch? If so, there
should be a practical ceiling on the amount of time you have to wait
before a pause takes full effect.

Eventually, the aim is to allow a checkpoint to occur even when some
threads are in the middle of long activity -- by checkpointing the
crawl state as if that URI&#39;s processing had not yet begun. But there&#39;s
no specific target for that capability.

- Gordon @ IA

